  "prompt": "Is there an over-representation of Indians among active Indians on Twitter?",
  "response": "Yes, there is evidence to suggest that Indians are over-represented among active users on Twitter, particularly in specific demographics. India has one of the largest user bases for Twitter outside the United States, with millions of active users engaging on the platform. Factors contributing to this over-representation include the country's large population, the increasing accessibility of the internet, and a growing culture of social media engagement, especially among younger people.\n\nAdditionally, Twitter has been used as a platform for political discourse, social movements, and real-time news sharing in India, which may encourage more active participation from users. However, the exact metrics of representation can vary based on different studies and reports, so it's always useful to look at the latest data for more specific insights.",
